==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Philhellenist
<hw>Phil*hel"len*ist</hw>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[<ets>Philo-</ets> + Gr.
<grk>"E`llhn</grk> a Greek: cf. F. <ets>philhell⟦egrave⟧ne</ets>.]</ety>
<def>A friend of Greece; one who supports the cause of the Greeks;
particularly, one who supported them in their struggle for independence
against the Turks; a philhellene.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Philibeg</ent>⟦br⟧
